text.tspan: Civil engineering student seeking an internship in structural or geotechnical engineering. Offer hands-on
experience in construction along with education in civil engineering principles and tools. Driven and
dedicated work ethic with solid communication and leadership skills. Dedicated to using critical thinking
and innovative design abilities to assist in developing successful projects.
Assisted project engineers in four projects with grading and roadway design, stormwater management
system design and erosion and sediment control design.
Accompanied senior technical staff for 12 on-site inspections during construction, learning how to
communicate design requirements with contractors and equipment suppliers.
Tested 35% of soils and materials to determine foundation strength.
Collected and entered 40% of site data and applied technical principles and theories to design
Collaborated in the preparation of charts and graphics included within design proposals for
Applied analytical mathematics to assist an engineering staff of 10 in compiling blueprints and plans.
Conducted 45% of code research under the supervision of engineering staff to write specifications and
Estimated materials costs and sourcing requirements for project feasibility.
Answered and transferred an average of 35 incoming telephone calls, taking messages for various staff
